    safety-in-expectation is when an algorithm is expected to achieve the value of the game on a sufficiently long timescale. strategy pi_i is safe if for every opponent strategy pi_{-i} and sufficiently large Q
    
    lim_{Q->\inf} (sum_{T=0}^{Q} v_i - u_i(pi_i, pi_{-i})) / Q -> 0
    
    RWYW is safe in expectation. 
    
