    Expected distance in n steps is O(sqrt(N)) in a 1d random walk.
    
    This is a bit different, bc there is a strong cap, but we can think of this as an absolute value, which makes no difference for the difference. This means O(sqrt(N)) is an upper bound, meaning the weaker sense is true.
    
    
